[thinking] **Considering Java Module Exports**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about Java module exports and how unnamed modules work. It seems like if a module isn't defined, it might still have access under certain conditions. If the target package isn't exported, is it still valid to call `Module.addExports`? I wonder if it’s allowed if the module is open. I'm curious about these rules since they can really affect how modules interact and function. There's a lot to consider!
[thinking] 
