[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Java Module Exports**\n\nI'm thinking about Java module exports and how unnamed modules work. It seems like if a module isn't defined, it might still have access under certain conditions. If the target package isn't exported, is it still valid to call `Module.addExports`? I wonder if it’s allowed if the module is open. I'm curious about these rules since they can really affect how modules interact and function. There's a lot to consider!\n\n**Evaluating ModelMapper options**\n\nI'm considering using the current class in ModelMapper's automatic module by running tests on the classpath. It seems like the native report uses JVM classpath, but I'm not sure about the module path. I think I could generate a subclass loaded in the package jdk.internal.misc. However, I wonder if the classloader can define java.* packages — probably not, but might allow jdk.internal.*. If I define a package in a named module, it should align with the caller's module. I'll need to explore this further.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03dc36b585fb3d800169f1be6ed11881959ba87fa6dd71ec64\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8b6Om0jZqNtPg7-N6um-XOI7yA1xEkB-CcPRXHrMrYG4Y7-3lKSe4hyPOMX3GagRPv_nJFLjBanzwdcBOXMmYRwAn-861mvf7g8EW9HZS3Y4GRGueKse768_ATtwKnBkG1TF8Gd9YRMJUiAnZugTZqLDt-QgOn2Tx3IYZVrHP2CDKXIY3Tsgx7zIIyrLJ3wIOYkEZBF404njvzAW9TySBIdyHVnB5KotzdDp3RuW86_K5jTU6i7Q6JcGsbfJkExwAoF262kI6uLeWfpwJc5slmoLu_eeBf10NOgiJ7oMspH2W-VaJi6oSXusE-iN4E5pPDeX5QkTf5PFJOetCFucOLfom0L4s4vyPdzAG71VDKKH96eZVR-PRmQ9JIVskcH-gOcJIZ82ND756wKzGaror_0pUb8HOzTy_r-5N57xD4eyJyESNOhcxOBvAuNo1qPREfUCwbM4EBQQQgtvkMeYddFLaYdAqfnt3tRodlVWaTLTe1-O-0E0V6asELSdzLt47DdYA6UPN3WcTo6CHtSzr3qpDpucfrPGn0QcLebpnNt0GITQlCohxvGMMJB6SETuYptyJ3a9I00AAsuop6NJCFAwgk7rAT_u3XFJTjDeWpWmeUVL22ImGuCLZ_NXPd-C0a3KjORHZOfi3_wrnnxFMf2i8_XlmlGcV4It9v9w7SOky_3Wj78FK3cU1EeK_n9vH0rhtwhXMpk_o9aMGxO7ZWNUnwAy5G6NrU2PQqa